The paper discusses the use of P2P networks for cybercrime, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the design and implementation of a P2P monitoring and crawling toolset, which involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the need for investigating P2P based systems, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and cyber forensics (cs.CY).
